  "title": "HYDRAULIC/MECHANICAL SERVICE ENGINEER",
  "description": "<p><strong>HYDRAULIC/MECHANICAL SERVICE ENGINEER</strong></p><p><strong>Job Scope</strong></p><p>· To lead a team to undertake service work on hydraulic cranes, winches, davits and other hydraulic equipment on board vessel</p><p>· Must be hands on with work </p><p>· Ensure all service activities are carried out with a high standard of safety & quality mindset</p><p>· Troubleshoot hydraulic problems and read and understand hydraulic schematics drawings for repair of hydraulic equipment</p><p>· Overhauling of hydraulic pumps, motors, flow pressure, directional control components, and cylinders</p><p>· Installation of hydraulic hoses on vessel</p><p>· Working on board a vessel or shipyard and overseas if required</p><p>· Troubleshooting of electrical related work such as electrical shock panel, electrical starter panel, control panel, PLC to hydraulic power pack and hydraulic system, if able will help</p><h2>Requirements </h2><p>o 5-8 years of hydraulic experience relating to servicing of marine hydraulic cranes, winches, hatch cover system, stearing gear system, davits etc. </p><p>o Posses hands on knowledge on pumps, motors, cylinders and hydraulic components</p><p>o Able to work independently for troubleshooting of hydraulic equipment on ships</p><p>o Able to read hydraulic schematic drawings and understand fully for repair of the hydraulic equipment </p><p>o Engineer working in existing hydraulic service company, hydraulic manufacturing company and shipyards can apply </p><p>o Minimum diploma in mechanical engineering from relevant polytechnic in Singapore or overseas OR relevant working experience with a OEM of hydraulic equipment or a hydraulic servicing company can apply.</p><p>o Able to work at anchorage and overseas if necessary</p><p>o Able to work 5.5 days and weekends if required</p><p>Salary: $3.5K - $4.5K</p>",
